<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-710-767  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 710 767.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  Dec 1990 v27 n12 p11(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Trends in intrabuilding show fiber advantages. (intrabuildingwiring) (includes related article on photonics)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Morgan, James H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The transition from electronics using copper wiring, to the newphotonics fiber world is underway, but it is too early to just usefiber, and too late to exclusively install copper.andP;  The mostappropriate way to plan for the future of a telecommunicationsystem is to allow for flexibility,.andP;  The minimum plan to eachdesktop should be 4 UTP + 4 UTP minimum, with 2 fibers optional,and up to 4 + 4 + 4 +4UTP, + 4-12 fibers.andP;  Two fibers arenecessary because the new Fiber Distributed Data Interface (FDDI)local area networks may come directly to the desktops.andP;  A 62.5/125micron, multi-mode fiber should be used.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     NetworksBusiness PlanningTelecommunicationsTrendsMicrocomputersWorkstationsCommunications ManagementFiber optics.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>